The paper focuses on generating human images based on given poses and backgrounds, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. The use of appearance features, pose features, and background features to generate images involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments on COCO and LIP datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research, further supporting the likelihood of cs.CV as the most likely category.
